{"title_page": "Azerbaijanis' Cultural Center", "text_new": "{{Infobox company | name = Azerbaijanis' Cultural Center\n| logo = \n| type = [[Non-governmental organisation|Non-Governmental Organisation]] \n| foundation = 2006\n| location = [[Marneuli]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]\n| key_people = [[Fazil Hasanov (chairman)|Fazil Hasanov]]\n| products = Education and culture \n| homepage = {{url|http://www.amm.ge}}\n}}\n\n'''Azerbaijanis' Cultural Center''' ('''ACC''') ({{lang-az|Az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar\u0131n M\u0259d\u0259niyy\u0259t M\u0259rk\u0259zi}}) is a non-governmental organization, which was founded in 2006, after [[Fazil Hasanov]], actual chairman of center, issued an appeal to [[Ilham Aliyev]], President of Azerbaijan and [[Mikheil Saakashvili]], President of Georgia during their meeting in [[Marneuli]]. One of the main objectives of ACC is the integration of local Azerbaijanis to Georgian civil society.\n\n==Activity==\n\n===Culture===\nThe center publishes \"[[Meydan (magazine)|Meydan]]\" and \"[[Qarapapaqlar]]\" magazines and \"[[Region Press]]\" newspaper. [[Sarvan (dance collective)|\"Sarvan\"]] folk-dance group, Azerbaijani writers union, library, etc. also function under the ACC.\n\n\"Sarvan\" dance ensemble was created by support of [[Heydar Aliyev Foundation]] in 2008. It won the first place in a nomination of \"Solo performance\" and the second place in a nomination of \"Collective performance\" in the \"[[Open New World 2009]]\". It is also supported by various Georgian and Azerbaijanis' government bodies, including [[Ministry of Culture and Monument Protection (Georgia)|The Ministry of Culture and Monument Protection of Georgia]], [[State Ministry for Reintegration (Georgia)|The State Ministry for Reintegration of Georgia]] and [[State Committee on Work with Diaspora (Azerbaijan)|The State Committee on Work with Diaspora of Azerbaijan Republic]].<ref>[https://sia.az/search.php?query=Az%C9%99rbaycanl%C4%B1lar%C4%B1n+M%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t+M%C9%99rk%C9%99zi Az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar\u0131n M\u0259d\u0259niyy\u0259t M\u0259rk\u0259zi]{{in lang|az}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nACC conducts different educational programmes, including Georgian and English language courses and IT workshops.<ref>[http://www.trend.az/news/society/1295181.html \u0414\u043b\u044f \u0430\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0435\u0432 \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u044b \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u044b \u0433\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430]{{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\n==Collaboration==\nACC collaborates with Islamic Development Bank, which provide financial support for Azerbaijanis' students in Georgia.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120315101132/http://www.diversity.ge/eng/resources.php?coi=0%7C15%7C17%7C17 Azerbaijanis Cultural Center in Marneuli]{{in lang|en}}\n\n[[Category:Azerbaijani culture]]\n[[Category:Ethnic organisations based in Georgia (country)]]\n[[Category:Cultural centers]]\n[[Category:Diaspora organizations]]\n\n\n{{Azerbaijan-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company | name = Azerbaijanis' Cultural Center\n| logo = \n| type = [[Non-governmental organisation|Non-Governmental Organisation]] \n| foundation = 2006\n| location = [[Marneuli]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]\n| key_people = [[Fazil Hasanov (chairman)|Fazil Hasanov]]\n| products = Education and culture \n| homepage = {{url|http://www.amm.ge}}\n}}\n\n'''Azerbaijani's Cultural Center''' ('''ACC''') ({{lang-az|Az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar\u0131n M\u0259d\u0259niyy\u0259t M\u0259rk\u0259zi}}) is a non-governmental organization, which was founded in 2006, after [[Fazil Hasanov]], actual chairman of center, issued an appeal to [[Ilham Aliyev]], President of Azerbaijan and [[Mikheil Saakashvili]], President of Georgia during their meeting in [[Marneuli]]. One of the main objectives of ACC is the integration of local Azerbaijanis to Georgian civil society.\n\n==Activity==\n\n===Culture===\nThe center publishes \"[[Meydan (magazine)|Meydan]]\" and \"[[Qarapapaqlar]]\" magazines and \"[[Region Press]]\" newspaper. [[Sarvan (dance collective)|\"Sarvan\"]] folk-dance group, Azerbaijani writers union, library, etc. also function under the ACC.\n\n\"Sarvan\" dance ensemble was created by support of [[Heydar Aliyev Foundation]] in 2008. It won the first place in a nomination of \"Solo performance\" and the second place in a nomination of \"Collective performance\" in the \"[[Open New World 2009]]\". It is also supported by various Georgian and Azerbaijanis' government bodies, including [[Ministry of Culture and Monument Protection (Georgia)|The Ministry of Culture and Monument Protection of Georgia]], [[State Ministry for Reintegration (Georgia)|The State Ministry for Reintegration of Georgia]] and [[State Committee on Work with Diaspora (Azerbaijan)|The State Committee on Work with Diaspora of Azerbaijan Republic]].<ref>[https://sia.az/search.php?query=Az%C9%99rbaycanl%C4%B1lar%C4%B1n+M%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t+M%C9%99rk%C9%99zi Az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar\u0131n M\u0259d\u0259niyy\u0259t M\u0259rk\u0259zi]{{in lang|az}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nACC conducts different educational programmes, including Georgian and English language courses and IT workshops.<ref>[http://www.trend.az/news/society/1295181.html \u0414\u043b\u044f \u0430\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0435\u0432 \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u044b \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u044b \u0433\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430]{{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\n==Collaboration==\nACC collaborates with Islamic Development Bank, which provide financial support for Azerbaijanis' students in Georgia.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120315101132/http://www.diversity.ge/eng/resources.php?coi=0%7C15%7C17%7C17 Azerbaijanis Cultural Center in Marneuli]{{in lang|en}}\n\n[[Category:Azerbaijani culture]]\n[[Category:Ethnic organisations based in Georgia (country)]]\n[[Category:Cultural centers]]\n[[Category:Diaspora organizations]]\n\n\n{{Azerbaijan-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CuriousGolden", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerbaijanis%27_Cultural_Center"}
{"title_page": "Twoja twarz brzmi znajomo", "text_new": "{{About||other versions of this series|Your Face Sounds Familiar|the current season|Twoja twarz brzmi znajomo (season 13)}}\n\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = Twoja twarz brzmi znajomo\n| image              = \n| genre              = [[Reality Television|Reality]]\n| picture_format     = [[16:9]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format       = [[Stereo]]\n| runtime            = \n| presenter          = [[Piotr G\u0105sowski]] <br> Maciej Dowbor \n| judges             = [[Ma\u0142gorzata Walewska]] <small>(''1\u2013'')</small><br/>[[Katarzyna Skrzynecka]] <small>(''2\u2013'')</small><br/>Kacper Kuszewski <small>(''9\u2013'')</small><br>Adam Strycharczuk <small>(''13\u2013'')</small><br/>Pawe\u0142 Kr\u00f3likowski <small>(''1\u201312'')</small><br/></small>[[Bart\u0142omiej Kasprzykowski]] <small>(''5\u20138'')</small><br>DJ Adamus <small>(''1\u20134'')</small><br/>Katarzyna Kwiatkowska <small>(''1'')</small>\n| country            = Poland\n| language           = Polish\n| network            = [[Polsat]]\n| num_seasons        = 13\n| num_episodes       = 131\n| location           = \n| executive_producer = \n| first_aired        = 8 March 2014\n| last_aired         = present\n| producer           = \n| related            = \n| website            = \n| website_title      = \n}}\n\n'''''Twoja twarz brzmi znajomo''''' is a Polish [[talent show]] developed by [[Polsat]] and based on the [[Your Face Sounds Familiar|Spanish]] series. The show is presented by [[Piotr G\u0105sowski]] and Maciej Dowbor, whilst the judging panel consists of Kacper Kuszewski, [[Ma\u0142gorzata Walewska]], Adam Strycharczuk and [[Katarzyna Skrzynecka]].\n\nThe show involves eight celebrities (singers, actors and television personalities) portraying various iconic singers each week to win 10,000 PLN for their chosen charity.\n\n==Format==\nThe show challenges celebrities (singers and actors) to impersonate different music artists every week, which are chosen by the show's \"Randomiser\". Afterwards they are judged by the panel of celebrity judges. The 'randomiser' can choose any older or younger artist available in the machine, or even a singer of the opposite sex, or a deceased singer. The winner of each episode wins 10,000 PLN, and the winner of the whole show wins 100,000 PLN. All money goes for a charity of their choice.\n\n===Voting===\nThe contestants are awarded points from the judges (and each other) based on their singing and dance routines. The points go from 1 to 7 and 10, with 10 being the judge's favorite of the night. After that, each contestant gives 5 points to a fellow contestant of their choice (known as \"Bonus\" points). The judges' score is combined with the \"Bonus\" points.\n\n==Cast==\n\n===Hosts===\n;Key\n:{{Color box|orange|border=darkgray}} Main host\n:{{Color box|lightblue|border=darkgray}} Contestant\n:{{Color box|#ffc6c6|border=darkgray}} Back-up host\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=\"180\" rowspan=\"2\"| Host !! colspan=13 text-align:center;| Season\n|-\n! width=\"70\" |1 !! width=\"70\" |2 !! width=\"70\" |3 !! width=\"70\" |4 !! width=\"70\" |5 !! width=\"70\" |6 !! width=\"70\" |7 !! width=\"70\" |8 !! width=\"70\" |9 !! width=\"70\" |10 !! width=\"70\" |11 !! width=\"70\" |12 !! width=\"70\" |13\n|-\n| [[Piotr G\u0105sowski]]|| colspan=13 style=\"text-align:center; background:orange;\"| \n|-\n| Maciej Dowbor|| colspan=13 style=\"text-align:center; background:orange;\"| \n|-\n| Zofia Zborowska||  colspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;background:white| || style=\"text-align:center; background:lightblue;\"|  || colspan=1 style=\"text-align:center; background:#ffc6c6;\"| || colspan=8 style=\"text-align:center;background:white|\n|-\n| Agnieszka Popielewicz||  colspan=4 style=\"text-align:center;background:white|  || colspan=1 style=\"text-align:center; background:#ffc6c6;\"| || colspan=8 style=\"text-align:center;background:white|\n|}\n\n===J